Why would we error in this case... I expected _both_ the status poll and the encrypt response to be able to update the apiserver's view of the current write key:
* We poll status periodically so if the write key changes, we bound how long we go without realizing it, even if no encrypting writes are being made
* We also look at the key id returned from encrypt responses, so we immediately know if a new write key is in use

That's how the fields in the API seem to be documented

```proto
message StatusResponse {
...
    // the current write key, used to determine staleness of data updated via value.Transformer.TransformFromStorage.
    string key_id = 3;
...
message EncryptResponse {
...
    // The KMS key ID used to encrypt the data. This must always refer to the KMS KEK and not any local KEKs that may be in use.
    // This can be used to inform staleness of data updated via value.Transformer.TransformFromStorage.
    string key_id = 2;
```

