this makes `completions` completely mutable for non-indexed jobs (even able to be changed from a set value to nil). that doesn't match what is described in the KEP. I expected something more like this:

```go
// CompletionMode is defaulted, we can count on it being non-nil
if *spec.CompletionMode != batch.IndexedCompletion {
  // only indexed jobs are allowed to change completions
  return apivalidation.ValidateImmutableField(spec.Completions, oldSpec.Completions, fldPath.Child("completions"))
}

// Parallelism is defaulted, we can count on it being non-nil.
// Completions is not defaulted, so guard against nil (which is caught by validateJobSpec)
// A non-nil value for completions must match spec.Parallelism
if spec.Completions != nil && *oldSpec.Completions != *spec.Completions && *spec.Parallelism != *spec.Completions {
  allErrs = append(allErrs, field.Invalid(fldPath, spec.Completions, ...
}
```

