> because kustomize is independently maintained and released, we were free to make breaking changes accordingly as long as we communicate exactly what the changes are.

But... it's *not* really independent since it gets pulled back into kubectl, and since kubectl supports limited skew to the apiserver, people don't really have the choice to stay on an old kubectl to keep previous kustomize behavior.

